<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id78438af3-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5" identifier="/us/usc/t16/s554"><num value="554">§ 554.</num><heading> Forest supervisors and rangers</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Forest supervisors and rangers shall be selected, when practicable, from qualified citizens of the States or Territories in which the national forests, respectively, are situated.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id78438af4-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">(<ref href="/us/act/1905-02-01/ch288/s3">Feb. 1, 1905, ch. 288, § 3</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/33/628">33 Stat. 628</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="id78438af5-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="id78438af6-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="id78438af7-6992-11f1-ab3f-8b4c043f8cd5"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">“National forests” substituted in text for “reserves” on authority of <ref href="/us/act/1907-03-04/ch2907">act Mar. 4, 1907, ch. 2907</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/34/1269">34 Stat. 1269</ref>, which provided that forest reserves shall hereafter be known as national forests.</p>
</note>
</notes>
